## Recent EleutherAI Research

EleutherAI has been investigating sparse autoencoders that recover interpretable, monosemantic features, and developing techniques for generating and scoring arbitrary text explanations of SAE features with an open source library.

Open source models generate and evaluate text explanations of SAE features reasonably well, though somewhat worse than closed models like Claude 3.5 Sonnet. Automatically interpreting 1.5M features of GPT-2 with their current pipeline would cost $1300 in API calls to Llama 3.1 or $8500 with Claude 3.5 Sonnet.

