    "notes": "The three seed papers form a tight cluster \u2014 all empirical SAE-for-interpretability work in the Anthropic tradition, spanning a one-layer proof-of-concept (Cunningham et al.), the canonical large-scale SAE paper (Towards Monosemanticity), and the frontier scale-up to Claude 3 Sonnet (Scaling Monosemanticity) \u2014 confirming a dictionary-learning-first, empiricism-first style. The current question about feature transfer and L1 alternatives is well-supported by active 2025\u20132026 literature (SAEBench, JumpReLU, e2e SAE, MetaSAEs, the canonical-units critique), so the interests list was tuned to retrieve both the mainstream and the critical/evaluative work. Sources were chosen to cover four active poles of this community: Anthropic-empirical (transformer-circuits.pub), commercial interpretability labs (Goodfire), mechanistic-safety labs (Apollo), and open-source community (EleutherAI blog, Neuronpedia, MATS); all URLs were fetched and confirmed active in 2025\u20132026."
