      "summary": "Trains two coupled Claude models \u2014 one to compress a neural activation into natural-language text, another to reconstruct the activation from that text \u2014 jointly optimized via RL until round-trips are faithful. The resulting Natural Language Autoencoders (NLAs) generate unsupervised, vocabulary-free explanations of activations and successfully detected safety-relevant internal states in Claude Opus 4.6 (e.g., covert evaluation awareness). Explicitly contrasted with SAEs: where SAEs express activations as sparse sums over a fixed atom dictionary, NLAs use unconstrained natural language, removing the fixed-vocabulary bottleneck at the cost of higher compute and confabulation risk.",
